        "product_description": {
            "value": [
                {
                    "language_tag": "en_US",
                    "value": "From cable management and food storage to school supplies and pantry organization, ToolTreaux’s 24 pack of food grade silicone zip ties or twist ties can do it all and will prove handy to have around the house, home office, workplace, or garage for a multitude of tasks. And, the best part? The zip ties are totally reusable.<br/><br/>Home offices, living room media centers, workshops, labs—these spaces, especially if cables are involved, can get messy fast. Whether it’s tripping over an extension cord, or getting your HDMI cable tangled, you need a cable management tool set to clear up space and make your space more organized. ToolTreaux’s environmentally friendly zip ties are the perfect tools for cord organization and cable management. You’ll be amazed at how much room you’ll save by using our twist ties to organize your messy entertainment set or home office. That’s how ToolTreaux’s reusable, multi-color cable ties are creating neater, more efficient rooms, one home, office or workplace at a time.<br/><br/>Now, we did say multipurpose; next stop: food prep and organization. The twist ties, zip ties or straps are made of high-temperature resistant silicone, which means that they are completely safe to use when preparing food in the kitchen (food grade). Even better, the multipurpose cable ties are reusable so you can use them to keep coffee fresh, blanch vegetables or organize your pantry. <br/><br/>Our 24-piece tool set of reusable silicone zip ties will last long in to the future and make your life more convenient and organized. However small or large your organizational project may be, be sure to have a pack of these twist ties on hand and you’ll be well on your way to a neat, tidy, clutter-free and organized space.",
                    "marketplace_id": "ATVPDKIKX0DER"
                }
            ],
            "is_required": true,
            "source": "catalog",
            "asin": "B0933RJK56",
            "raw_value": true
